We recommended to the Local Chief Executive the following:

3. The GSO-Designate to secure cost of the received goods without value during the year from the DOH-XI and PHO Davao del Sur or cost these goods using its fair market value and submit a copy of the report to the Municipal Accounting Office (MACCO) for recording in the books;

4. The GSO-Designate and MHO to conduct an inventory count on the remaining goods received from DOH XI and PHO Davao del Sur;

5. The MHO to prepare Requisition and Issue Slip (RIS) on the utilization of these received goods without cost from the DOH XI and PHO Davao del Sur during the year and submit the RIS to the GSO;

6. The GSO-Designate to prepare SSMI based on the RIS submitted by the MHO and submit the report to the MACCO for recording in the books;


7. The Municipal Accountant to book all unrecorded goods without cost received and utilized/ consumed during the year based on the report submitted by the GSO; and


8. Henceforth, for the GSO to submit report on all goods received/donated from other government agencies and its issuances to MACCO for recording in the books of the Municipality.

We recommended to the Local Chief Executive:

16. Thru the Municipal Health Officer to consider additional manpower to the Health Office to handle, in particular, the receipts and issuances of all inventories (from the custody to the reportorial aspect) for both the receipts from donations and regular purchases including compliance to the routine storage management task as prescribed by the DOH WOM;

17. Thru the MHO Inventory In-charge/ Supply Officer to prepare the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) periodically and submit the same to the GSO- Designate for consolidation and submission to the Accounting Office;

18. To create an Inventory Committee who will be responsible in the conduct of the inventory taking of supplies and materials at least twice a year and prepare the RCPI and submit the same to COA within the deadline set;

19. Properly organize the medical commodities especially stored in the lying-in facility and install inventory system on the receipt and issuances of all supplies from all the storages; and

20. Assess the viability of constructing a warehouse within the Municipality’s premise to house all the medical inventories for proper safekeeping prescribed by the DOH WOM.

